SP  - 5
EP  - 38
VL  - 54
IS  - 1
KW  - forward premium puzzle
KW  - uncovered interest parity
KW  - futures rates
KW  - price of risk
KW  - currency excess returns
KW  - capital asset pricing model
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-2879
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jmcb.12872
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract The use of futures instead of forwards exchange contracts completes the maturity spectrum of the correlation between spot yields and the premium. We find that the forward premium puzzle appears to be a precrisis phenomenon and is only observed for maturities longer than about 1 month. Differences in the exposure to risk help to explain cross-sectional spreads in currency excess returns. However, this only applies for medium and longer maturities. Considering that most studies that test the validity of a risk-based approach to currency excess returns focus on short maturity securities, this explains why this approach is so often rejected.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Term Structure of Uncertainty: New Evidence from Survey Expectations
AU  - BINDER, CAROLA
AU  - MCELROY, TUCKER S.
AU  - SHENG, XUGUANG S.
Y1  - 2022/02/01
PY  - 2022
DA  - 2022/02/01
