KW  - liquidity facility
KW  - systemic liquidity risk
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-2879
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jmcb.12806
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract Money is both the medium for transaction and the most liquid asset for banks. We examine both roles of money in an integrated framework, where banks are subject to aggregate illiquidity risk. An active central bank can replicate the constrained efficient allocation, which, however, cannot be implemented in the market equilibrium: due to moral hazard problems, banks invest excessively in illiquid assets, forcing the central bank to provide liquidity at low interest rates. An interest rate policy aiming to reduce systemic liquidity risk is dynamically inconsistent. Instead, the constrained efficiency can be achieved by imposing ex ante liquidity coverage requirement.
ER  - 

